<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-09-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-09-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="899" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d899">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 891.001.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Persian
                                Chargé</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-09-23"><hi rend="italic">September 23,
                                    1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your announcement of the death of His Imperial Highness the Regent has
                            been received by me with great regret. Accept an expression of my
                            sympathy.</p>
                        <p>The President has by telegraph conveyed his condolence to His Imperial
                            Majesty the Shah, and the Secretary of State has also telegraphed in the
                            same sense to the minister of foreign affairs of Persia.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>